## User Journey (End-to-End)

### A. Onboarding

1. User signs up via Google OAuth
2. Quick onboarding modal: platform choice, goals
3. Lands in clean workspace with checklist

### B. First Action → Add Lead

1. Clicks "+ Add Lead"
2. Enters name, brand, contact channel, note
3. Lead appears in Contacts under "New"
4. Opens detail panel with click

### C. Lead to Deal Conversion

1. Opens lead card
2. Clicks "Convert to Deal"
3. Fills offer, deliverables, deadline
4. Automatically moves to Deal Pipeline "Negotiating"

### D. Daily Workflow

1. Morning: Dashboard shows tasks, leads, deals, content
2. Completes tasks, adds notes, moves deals
3. Dashboard becomes command center

### E. Content Planning

1. Opens Content Calendar
2. Adds content idea
3. Links to deal (if sponsored)
4. Updates status: Idea → Draft → Posted

### F. Closing a Deal

1. Drags deal to "Completed"
2. Confirms amount + notes
3. Revenue updates on dashboard
4. Deal archived but viewable

### G. Notes Usage

1. Stores pitch templates
2. Saves negotiation notes
3. Keeps content scripts
4. Tags and searches

